cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the extraction of geo-social data, which involves the use of algorithms and techniques from several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on mining patterns and recommendations from social data. The paper also deals with data extraction and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The use of search algorithms and clustering techniques suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
